              <br><br>
               Follow these directions for creating an additional skin directory (XPBlue) for the Windows XP Mobile v4.0 Blue Scheme) via P2KTools v0.6.3.0:<br />
<br />
1. Download the flex file zip required to make additional directories:<br />
<br />
<a href="http://68.11.62.254:2333/flash/Netuddki_flex.zip">Netuddki_flex.zip</a><br />
<br />
2. Extract all *.hs files to some directory.<br />
<br />
3. Open Motorola PST (6.7_GENERAL)<br />
- Go to File &gt; Open &gt; pFlex<br />
- Browse to directory containing *.hs files, select XPBlue.hs and press the &quot;Open&quot; button.<br />
- A dialog entitled &quot;pFLEX&quot; will open. Just hit the &quot;Run&quot; button.<br />
(PST will suspend your phone, and the flex will be added.)<br />
<br />
4. Success message will display. Close PST.<br />
<br />
5. Open Bezol's <a href="http://68.11.62.254:2333/apps/P2KTools_v0.6.3.0.zip">P2KTools v0.6.3.0</a><br />
- Change to P2K Mode (if necessary)<br />
- Connect (press the &quot;Connect&quot; button.)<br />
- Optional: Press the &quot;Refresh&quot; button (left side, below) to view phone's directory tree.<br />
- Using the &quot;Use upload path&quot; field at the lower left, type &quot;/a/mobile/skins/XPBlue/&quot;<br />
- Press &quot;Upload&quot; button (left, middle)<br />
- (Browse dialog opens.) Go to your Windows XP Mobile Blue v4.0 &quot;skins&quot; folder and rename (if necessary) your skin files to:<br />
<br />
XPBlue1.dat<br />
XPBlue2.dat<br />
XPBlue.dat<br />
XPBlue.ski<br />
<br />
When renaming is complete, select all skins files in directory and press the &quot;Open&quot; button.<br />
<br />
- P2KTools will automatically create<br />
the &quot;XPBlue&quot; folder under your phone's &quot;/a/mobile/skins&quot; directory and upload the skin files (all with file attribute 07000000; world readable/writeable)<br />
<br />
6. (Optional) Bring your phone out of suspend mode, re-connect to P2KTools, and refresh the directory tree to verify that the XPBlue skin directory now exists and that the skin files (*.dat, .ski) exist within.<br />
<br />
7. Bring your phone out of suspend mode (if necessary), go to Settings &gt; Personalize &gt; Skin<br />
<br />
...and select XPBlue for your skin.<br />
<br />
See the readme.txt included with your Windows XP Mobile Blue ZIP to understand how to upload the wallpaper, theme, custom startup/shutdown graphics and sounds, etc.<br />
<br />
---<br />
<br />
Use this same process to add other skins to your phone.<br />
<br />
